      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: The lengthy recounting of other people's travels -- not, of course, our own -- is indeed boring and superfluous. But there's a better way of doing it: writing it all down.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: The lengthy recounting of other people's travels -- not, of course, our own -- is indeed boring and superfluous. But there's a better way of doing it: writing it all down.</p>
        <p>After printing out ''France: June 5 to 30, 1999'' you have photocopies made and mail them around to your friends. They can then lie about it convincingly the next time you meet, or (praises be!) compliment you on it -- while handing you a copy of their own, more elegant composition: ''Greece and the Isles: a Personal Odyssey.''</p>
        <p>CHARLES B. WHEELER  Columbus, Ohio</p>
      </block>
